<Author>emnadel
<Content>The City of New York should protest the use of its name We have lived in central Mexico for 18 years and go to Mexico City often. 6 of us tried the Hotel New York and were disappointed.The interior rooms are dark and dreary. Furniture is old and could be described as Salvation Army style. The bathrooms are small, and all of the water pipes are exposed. They don't give face towels, wash cloths, bathroom mat, tissues, bottled water or hairdryers.We have found better deals for a similar price. The carpet design was horrendous, and clashed with the bedspreads and draperies.The mattress was ok, but they don't have queen or king size beds. The choice is twin or double. The pillows were old and felt like cooked oatmeal. 
