<Author>Mimi_in_Brooklyn
<Content>Single Female Traveler Thumbs Up I traveled to Mexico City in April for four days as a single 25 year old female without a lick of Spanish. I felt very comfortable in this area of town on my own and was able to walk back and forth to the subway and resturants, etc. I found the staff helpful, and again, I speak no spanish. Not much in the way of ambiance but very clean. I even ate in the resturant once and while I wouldn't recommend it exactly, it was fine. My one complaint is that the hotel was a bit noisy at night. Thin walls and a room adjacent to an airshaft didn't help. But all in all, a good budget option. 
