<Author>shell_217
<Content>Good place, some drawbacks. After reading some reviews we decided that this place had easy access to the metro, which is does and that it is in a quiet street right off of one of the main streets, which it is. However, we felt that the short walk from the main street to the hotel was all too lonely at night and this made it difficult to move around at night after 9 pm if not with taxis who will overcharge you ridiculous amounts (what was a 2 dollar taxi ride going to a theater became a 12 dollar ride coming back because it was a 'night fee' they were charging). I recommend other hotels like Casa de la Condesa Reforma (in this same 'colonia') which is safer to be out and about at night.The New York, however, does have very clean installations which I am always picky about but our bed was really hard. The room is small but sufficient. We had our breakfast included but we realized afetr paying a lot for our first breakfact that you have to ask for your breakfast stub from the reception. 
