<Author>NAURU
<Content>Great value hotel in Mexico City I moved from an $80 US per night hotel, which was so noisy I couldn't sleep, to the New York Hotel, which was only $32 per night. Well, it was a great move, because the New York Hotel was just as nice, but extremely quiet, and had friendlier service, and was so much cheaper.  It is only about 200 metres from the Paseo de la Reforma, and about a 4 minute walk from the nearest subway (metro) station (Hidalgo). The price also includes a breakfast of eggs, toast and bacon/ham/sausage.  I found the area to be safe at night. I will definitely stay at the New York Hotel next time I go to Mexico City. 
