<Author>wudunn
<Content>Incredible value in a great neighborhood I'v stayed on and off in this neighborhood for more than 20 years. The Oxford Where I always stayed and loved was looking a little shabby(but probably still a good low budget choice for 12 bucks)so I chose the New York just around the corner -What a treat! My 300 peso single was nicer than any hundred dollar room any where - Great helpful staff (it helps to know a little spanish) and the 7 or 8 block area surrounding the hotel is one of the most charming (albeit a bit down at the heel) safe and comfortable parts of this chaotic city midway between the zocalo and the zona rosa just a few minutes walk to the alameda and the great little restaurant Cafe Trevi -As far as I'm concerned - One of the best hotel deals ever 
